[h1]The Elseif Statement[/h1]

Use the[b] if...elseif...else[/b] statement to specify a [b]new [/b]condition to test, if the first condition is [b]false[/b].
[b]
Syntax:[/b] [code format="php"][b]if [/b](condition) {
  code to be executed if condition is [b]true[/b];
} [b]elseif [/b](condition) {
  code to be executed if condition is [b]true[/b];
} [b]else [/b]{
   code to be executed if condition is [b]false[/b];
}[/code]
[note]You can add as many [b]elseif[/b] statements as you want. Just note, that the [b]elseif[/b] statement must begin with an [b]if[/b] statement.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to print "Male" if the variable "gender" is equal to 0, "Female" if it is equal to 1, and "Undefined" in all other cases.
[!raw!]
if($gender == {0})
   echo "Male";
{1}($gender {2} 1)
   echo "Female";
{3}
   echo "Undefined";

